HEADWORD: Xylograph
<hw>Xy"lo*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Xylo-</ets>
+ <ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety> <def>An engraving on wood, or the impression
from such an engraving; a print by xylography.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

